author: @RabeezRiaz
text: If you write %%time in the first line of the cell in a notebook it will print the execution time taken when cell runs. Even comments can‚Äôt come before the %%time   These are called magic functions btw and some of them even work in the ipython shell and not just jupyter.   Also if you run a cell with shift+enter it will run current cell and select the next cell. This is why you were getting that annoying scrolling. If you use ctrl+enter it doesn‚Äôt change cells after execution.
